  "decomposition_rationale": "The parent SimpleBookLibrary receives a command and book_data. It selects the appropriate child function based on the command (add, list, borrow, return, remove) and calls it with relevant parameters extracted from book_data. Each child performs its specific operation using global data stores (books and next_id) and returns a complete result dictionary with success, message, and data. The parent then returns this result unchanged. This decomposition keeps each child focused on one operation, satisfying the 'no cross-call' rule as parent orchestrates directly.",
  "interface_preservation": {
